solution:
Given $M=8 \times 10^{22} \mathrm{Am}^2$
$$
\mathrm{d}=\mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{e}}=6.4 \times 10^6 \mathrm{~m}
$$
Earth's magnetic field, $\mathrm{B}=\frac{\mu_0}{4 \pi} \cdot \frac{2 \mathrm{M}}{\mathrm{d}^3}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
&=\frac{4 \pi \times 10^{-7}}{4 \pi} \times \frac{2 \times 8 \times 10^{22}}{\left(6.4 \times 10^6\right)^3} \\
&\cong 0.6 \text { Gauss }
\end{aligned}
$$
